## How Sedo Works: The Three Ways to Buy and Sell

Sedo offers three distinct transaction methods for domain names. Understanding how each one works is essential before you jump in, especially at the price points where .ai domains tend to trade.

### Fixed Price Listings

The simplest option. A seller lists their domain at a set price, and any buyer can purchase it immediately by paying that amount. Think of it like a "Buy It Now" listing on eBay. There is no negotiation, no waiting. If the price is right, you click buy and the transaction begins.

For sellers, fixed-price listings work well when you have a clear sense of what your domain is worth and do not want to deal with back-and-forth offers. The downside is that you might leave money on the table if demand is higher than you expected. For buyers, fixed price is attractive because there is certainty. You know exactly what you will pay, and you do not risk losing the domain in a bidding war.

### Make an Offer (Negotiation)

This is the most common method for premium .ai domains on Sedo. The seller lists the domain, and interested buyers submit offers. The seller can accept, reject, or counter. Negotiations happen through Sedo's messaging system, which keeps both parties' identities private until a deal is struck.

