One thing to note: Sedo allows sellers to set a minimum offer threshold. If you submit an offer below that minimum, it will be automatically rejected. This filters out lowball offers and saves everyone time.

### Auctions

Sedo runs timed auctions where buyers compete openly. An auction has a start price, a set duration (usually 7 to 14 days), and may include a reserve price. When the auction ends, the highest bidder wins, provided any reserve price has been met.

Sedo auctions can be intense for desirable .ai domains. Bidding often starts slow and then heats up dramatically in the final hours. Sedo has an anti-sniping mechanism: if a bid is placed in the last few minutes, the auction extends slightly to give other bidders a chance to respond.

