If there is one universal rule in domain investing, it is this: shorter names sell for more money. This holds true across every TLD, and .ai is no exception. But the premium for brevity in .ai is particularly steep.

### Two-Character Domains: The Pinnacle

Two-character .ai domains sit at the top of the value pyramid. The numbers speak clearly:

- **hp.ai** sold for **$565,000** in 2019
- **os.ai** sold for **$150,000** in 2025
- **tp.ai** sold for **$90,000** in 2025
- **av.ai** sold for **$83,817** in 2019
- **bm.ai** sold for **$55,000** in 2026

Even the least expensive [two-letter](/blog/two-letter-ai-domains-value) .ai sales we have tracked come in at several thousand dollars. There are only 676 possible two-letter combinations using the alphabet, and only 1,296 if you include digits. That finite pool means every two-character .ai domain carries inherent scarcity value.

### Three to Four Character Domains

Step up to three and four characters and you are still in premium territory, though prices drop noticeably. Three-letter .ai domains regularly trade in the $5,000 to $50,000 range, depending on whether the letters form a recognizable acronym or abbreviation. Four-character domains that spell actual words (like "chat" or "data") can command six or even seven figures, but random four-letter strings trade for considerably less.

### Five Characters and Beyond

Longer .ai domains can still be extremely valuable, but only if they tick other boxes on this list. Voice.ai ($1.5M), Security.ai ($1M), and boyfriend.ai ($600K) are all longer names that commanded huge prices because of their dictionary word status and brandability. A random 10-character string, though? You might struggle to sell it for registration cost.

### The Length Premium in Numbers

Looking across our database, the average sale price for two-character .ai domains is roughly 8 to 10 times higher than the average for domains with five or more characters. Length is not everything, but it is the single most reliable predictor of baseline value.

