## 3. Brandability: Easy to Say, Spell, and Remember

A domain can be short and contain a real word, but if it is hard to pronounce or easy to misspell, its value takes a hit. Brandability is the "would this work on a billboard?" test.

### What Makes a .ai Domain Brandable?

The most brandable .ai domains share several traits:

- **Easy to say aloud.** You can tell someone the domain in conversation and they can type it without asking you to spell it. Get.ai ($909K) passes this test perfectly.
- **Easy to spell.** No ambiguous letter combinations, no hyphens, no numbers in odd places. Draw.ai ($500K) is crystal clear.
- **Memorable.** After hearing it once, you remember it. Speed.ai ($165K) sticks in the mind because the word itself is vivid and familiar.
- **Works as a brand name.** It sounds like a company, not a keyword string. "Welcome to Get.ai" sounds natural. "Welcome to acquisition-optimization.ai" does not.

### Brandability vs. Keyword Value

Sometimes brandability and keyword value align perfectly. Chat.ai ($1.2M) is both a high-volume keyword and an excellent brand name. But sometimes they diverge. A domain like "best-ai-chatbot-software.ai" might target a keyword, but it is terrible as a brand. Our data consistently shows that brandable names outsell keyword-stuffed names by wide margins.

### The "Radio Test"

Domain investors often use the "radio test": if you heard the domain on a podcast or radio ad, could you type it correctly on the first try? Domains that pass this test, like send.ai, play.ai, and grow.ai, consistently trade at premiums. Those that fail it (think domains with unusual spellings, numbers mixed with letters in confusing ways, or ambiguous pronunciations) trade at discounts.

### Real-World Brandability Winners

