### The Anchoring Effect

Comps also create psychological anchoring. When Chat.ai sells for $1.2 million, every other conversational or communication-related .ai domain gets a price anchor. Sellers of domains like Talk.ai, Speak.ai, or Converse.ai can point to Chat.ai as evidence that communication-themed .ai domains are worth six to seven figures.

This works in reverse too. If a comparable domain sold for less than expected, it can put downward pressure on similar names. The market is self-referencing, and each new sale adjusts expectations for similar domains.

