## Lessons for Buyers and Sellers

### For Buyers

**Expect to pay six figures minimum for any common single word.** The days of picking up well-known dictionary words as .ai domains for $10,000 or $20,000 are largely over. If the word appears in everyday conversation, budget at least $250,000.

**Tech relevance adds 2 to 3x to the price.** A tech-relevant word like "Cloud" or "Bot" will cost you two to three times what a comparable non-tech word would, because the .ai extension amplifies the word's meaning.

**Shorter words cost more, but they are worth it.** A three-letter single-word .ai domain averages over $800,000, while a six-letter word averages under $400,000. The extra investment in a shorter word pays dividends in brandability and memorability.

**Verbs are undervalued relative to nouns.** Action verbs like Build.ai ($270K), Create.ai ($260K), and Search.ai ($265K) trade at lower prices than comparable nouns but offer arguably better branding potential. A verb domain is a built-in call to action.

### For Sellers

